title: 820-2915 no CPU VCORE
message:
No corrosion.

Power rails all present and correct aside from:

PPVCORE_S0_CPU = 0V
PPVCCSA_S0_REG = 0.98 (not sure about this one)

Checked U7400
Pin 1, CPU_IMVP_VR_ON  = 3V3
Pin 2, CPUIMVP_TON = 12V5
Pin 15, 24,  PP5V_S0 = 5V

No idea where to go from here.

title: 820-2915 no CPU VCORE
message: This is going to suck. Try a donor BIOS and inspect board for physical damage. Also heat the GPU first to eliminate that.

title: 820-2915 no CPU VCORE
message:
Tried GPU but no go.
Tried replacing U7400 because it's not putting anything out to FET gates.
SPIROM is good.

Guess I'll check current sensing and look deeper into what's going on around U7400 circuits.

Any other ideas?

title: 820-2915 no CPU VCORE
message: Nooooo, U7400 is fine. U7400 needs communication with CPU to turn it on. This could really be anything. Check damaged components, was it dropped? Did you really try BIOS? Again this board will probably be a rabbit hole...
